algorithmSettings.name: seed
algorithmSettings.description: Integer seed for random number generator

algorithmSettings.name: failed_f_value
algorithmSettings.description: Return Value for F(x) if F fails

measures.name: residential_simulation_controls
measures.description: Set the simulation timesteps per hour, the run period begin month/day and end month/day, and the calendar year (for start day of week).
measures.modeler_description: Set the simulation timesteps per hour on the Timestep object, the run period begin month/day and end month/day on the RunPeriod object, and the calendar year on the YearDescription object.

arguments.name: timesteps_per_hr
arguments.description: The value entered here is the number of (zone) timesteps to use within an hour. For example a value of 6 entered here directs the program to use a zone timestep of 10 minutes and a value of 60 means a 1 minute timestep.

arguments.name: begin_month
arguments.description: This numeric field should contain the starting month number (1 = January, 2 = February, etc.) for the annual run period desired.

arguments.name: begin_day_of_month
arguments.display_name: Run Period Begin Day of Month
arguments.description: This numeric field should contain the starting day of the starting month (must be valid for month) for the annual run period desired.

arguments.name: end_month
arguments.description: This numeric field should contain the ending month number (1 = January, 2 = February, etc.) for the annual run period desired.

arguments.name: end_day_of_month
arguments.display_name: Run Period End Day of Month
arguments.description: This numeric field should contain the ending day of the ending month (must be valid for month) for the annual run period desired.

arguments.name: calendar_year
arguments.description: This numeric field should contain the calendar year that determines the start day of week. If you are running simulations using AMY weather files, the value entered for calendar year will not be used; it will be overridden by the actual year found in the AMY weather file.

measures.name: build_existing_model
measures.description: Builds the OpenStudio Model for an existing building.
measures.modeler_description: Builds the OpenStudio Model using the sampling csv file, which contains the specified parameters for each existing building. Based on the supplied building number, those parameters are used to run the OpenStudio measures with appropriate arguments and build up the OpenStudio model.

arguments.name: building_id
arguments.description: The building number (between 1 and the number of samples).

arguments.name: workflow_json
arguments.description: The name of the JSON file (in the resources dir) that dictates the order in which measures are to be run. If not provided, the order specified in resources/options_lookup.tsv will be used.

arguments.name: number_of_buildings_represented
arguments.description: The total number of buildings represented by the existing building models.

arguments.name: sample_weight
arguments.description: Number of buildings this simulation represents.

arguments.name: downselect_logic
arguments.description: Logic that specifies the subset of the building stock to be considered in the analysis. Specify one or more parameter|option as found in resources\options_lookup.tsv. When multiple are included, they must be separated by '||' for OR and '&&' for AND, and using parentheses as appropriate. Prefix an option with '!' for not.

arguments.name: measures_to_ignore
arguments.description: Measures to exclude from the OpenStudio Workflow specified by listing one or more measure directories separated by '|'. Core ResStock measures cannot be ignored (this measure will fail). INTENDED FOR ADVANCED USERS/WORKFLOW DEVELOPERS.

measures.name: apply_upgrade
measures.description: Measure that applies an upgrade (one or more child measures) to a building model based on the specified logic.
measures.modeler_description: Determines if the upgrade should apply to a given building model. If so, calls one or more child measures with the appropriate arguments.

arguments.name: upgrade_name
arguments.description: User-specificed name that describes the upgrade.

arguments.name: option_1
arguments.description: Specify the parameter|option as found in resources\options_lookup.tsv.

arguments.name: option_1_apply_logic
arguments.description: Logic that specifies if the Option 1 upgrade will apply based on the existing building's options. Specify one or more parameter|option as found in resources\options_lookup.tsv. When multiple are included, they must be separated by '||' for OR and '&&' for AND, and using parentheses as appropriate. Prefix an option with '!' for not.
